newsitem.title: LUXEMBOURG: Arafat arrives in Luxembourg for EU talks.
newsitem.headline: Arafat arrives in Luxembourg for EU talks.

text.p: Palestinian President Yasser Arafat arrived here on Monday for hastily-arranged talks with European Union foreign ministers on the threatened Middle East peace process.
Arafat met the ministers amid uncertainty whether he would continue to Washington for a summit with Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
Asked at the airport what he wanted from Netanyahu, Arafat told reporters:
"I am not asking for the moon, I am only asking for what had been agreed upon and what had been signed to be implemented accurately and honestly."

"The agreement which I had signed (was) not with the Labour Party, I signed it with the government of Israel. This had been accepted in the Knesset (the Israeli parliament), also it had been accepted in our legislative council and in our national council."
"So we are committed to it, the Israelis are committed to it, and we have to do our best to protect the peace process."
